[277.48127, "o", "\u001b[2;3HBy default CodeIgniter enables access to the $_GET array.  If for some \u001b[3;3Hreason you would like to disable it, set 'allow_get_array' to FALSE.    \u001b[4;2H\u001b[65X\u001b[5;3HWARNING: This feature is DEPRECATED and currently available only\u001b[6;3H         for backwards compatibility purposes! \r\n\n*/\u001b[71X\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'allow_get_array'\u001b[m\u000f] = TRUE;\u001b[20X\r\n \r\n/*\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[30X\r\n| Error Logging Threshold\r\n|--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[15;2H\u001b[74X\u001b[16;3HYou can enable error logging by setting a threshold over zero. The\u001b[17;2H threshold determines what gets logged. Threshold options are:\u001b[12X\u001b[19;3H      0 = Disables logging, Error logging TURNED OFF\u001b[19X\u001b[20;3H      1 = Error Messages (including PHP errors)\u001b[25X\u001b[21;3H      2 = Debug Messages\u001b[5X\u001b[22;2H       3 = Informational Messages\r\n|       4 = All Messages\r\n|\u001b[35X\r\n| You can also pass an array with threshold levels to show individual error types\r\n| \u001b[27;2H       array(2) = Debug Messages, without Error Messages\u001b[18X\u001b[28;2H\u001b[13X\n For a live site you'll usually only enable Errors (1) to be logged otherwise\u001b[30;2H your log files will fill up very fast.\u001b[31;2H\u001b[72X\r\n*/\u001b[73X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103m$config['lo\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mg_threshold'\u001b[m\u000f] = 0;\u001b[47X\r\n \r\n/*\u001b[45X\u001b[36;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[37;3HError Logging Directory Path\u001b[15X\u001b[38;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[39;2H\u001b[74X\r\n| Leave this BLANK unless you would like to set something other than the default\r\n| application/logs/ directory. Use a full server path with trailing slash.\r\n|\r\n*/\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103m$config['lo\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mg_path'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m''\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[50X\r\n\u001b[12X\n/*\u001b[73X\u001b[47;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[48;3HLog File Extension\u001b[58X\u001b[49;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[51;3HThe default filename extension for log files. The default 'php' allows for\r\n| protecting the log files via basic scripting, when they are to be stored\r\n| under a publicly accessible directory.\r\n|\r\n| Note: Leaving it blank will default to 'php'.\u001b[56;2H\u001b[74X\r\n*/\u001b[16X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103m$config['lo\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mg_file_extension'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m''\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[40X\r\n \r\n/*\u001b[69X\u001b[61;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[62;3HLog File Permissions\u001b[63;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n| \r\n| The file system permissions to be applied on newly created log files.\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f226,1          42\u001b[67;13H\u001b[?25h"]
