[360.37832, "o", "\u001b[H| Enabling this setting will tell CodeIgniter to look for a Composer\r\n| package auto-loader script in application/vendor/autoload.php.\r\n|\r\n|       $config['composer_autoload'] = TRUE;\u001b[5;2H\u001b[74X\u001b[6;3HOr if you have your vendor/ directory located somewhere else, you\u001b[7;2H can opt to set a specific path as well:\u001b[34X\u001b[9;3H      $config['composer_autoload'] = '/path/to/vendor/autoload.php';\u001b[10;2H\u001b[23X\n For more information about Composer, please visit http://getcomposer.org/\u001b[12;2H\u001b[26X\n Note: This will NOT disable or override the CodeIgniter-specific\u001b[14;3H      autoloading (application/config/autoload.php)\r\n*/\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'composer_autoload'\u001b[m\u000f] = FALSE;\u001b[36X\r\n\u001b[74X\n/*\u001b[64X\u001b[19;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[20;3HAllowed URL Characters\u001b[25X\u001b[21;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[22;2H\u001b[72X\u001b[23;3HThis lets you specify which characters are permitted within your URLs.\u001b[24;2H When someone tries to submit a URL with disallowed characters they will\r\n| get a warning message.\r\n|\u001b[104X\r\n| As a security measure you are STRONGLY encouraged to restrict URLs to\r\n| as few characters as possible.  By default only these are allowed: a-z 0-9~%.:_-\u001b[29;2H\u001b[74X\u001b[30;3HLeave blank to allow all characters -- but only if you are insane.\u001b[31;2H\u001b[74X\n The configured value is actually a regular expression character group\u001b[33;3Hand it will be executed as: ! preg_match('/^[\u001b[30m\u001b[103m<\u001b[m\u000fpermitted_uri_chars>]+$/i\u001b[34;2H\u001b[73X\u001b[35;3HDO NOT CHANGE THIS UNLESS YOU FULLY UNDERSTAND THE REPERCUSSIONS!!\u001b[38;10H\u001b[92mpermitted_uri_chars'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'a-z 0-9~%.:_\\-'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[42;3HEnable Query Strings\u001b[45;3HBy default CodeIgniter uses search-engine friendly segment based URLs: \u001b[46;3Hexample.com/who/what/where/\u001b[46X\u001b[47;2H\u001b[75X\n You can optionally enable standard query string based URLs:\u001b[49;3Hexample.com?who=me&what=something&where=here \u001b[50;2H\u001b[47X\u001b[51;3HOptions are: TRUE or FALSE (boolean)\u001b[7X\u001b[53;3HThe other items let you set the query string 'words' that will\u001b[11X\r\n| invoke your controllers and its functions:\r\n| example.com/index.php?c=controller&m=function\r\n|\r\n| Please note that some of the helpers won't work as expected when\u001b[58;2H this feature is enabled, since CodeIgniter is designed primarily to\u001b[6X\u001b[59;3Huse segment based URLs.\u001b[60;2H\u001b[74X\r\n*/\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'enable_query_strings'\u001b[m\u000f] = FALSE;\u001b[38X\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'controller_trigger'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'c'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[13X\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'function_trigger'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'm'\u001b[m\u000f;\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'directory_trigger'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'd'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[19X\u001b[66;224H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f56,48         26%\u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
[361.055751, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f?"]
[361.063225, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[30m\u001b[103m<?\u001b[m\u000fphp\u001b[63X\r\n\u001b[96mdefined\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'BASEPATH'\u001b[m\u000f) OR \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fexit\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'No direct script access allowed'\u001b[m\u000f); \r\n \r\n/*\u001b[42X\u001b[5;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[6;3HBase Site URL\u001b[52X\u001b[7;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[9;3HURL to your CodeIgniter root. Typically this will be your base URL, \u001b[10;2H WITH a trailing slash:\u001b[11;2H\u001b[74X\n       http://example.com/\u001b[13;2H\u001b[65X\u001b[14;3HWARNING: You MUST set this value!\u001b[18X\r\n| \r\n| If it is not set, then CodeIgniter will try guess the protocol and path\r\n| your installation, but due to security concerns the hostname will be set\r\n| to $_SERVER['SERVER_ADDR'] if available, or localhost otherwise.\u001b[19;2H The auto-detection mechanism exists only for convenience during\u001b[10X\u001b[20;3Hdevelopment and MUST NOT be used in production!\u001b[21;2H\u001b[74X\n If you need to allow multiple domains, remember that this file is still\u001b[23;3Ha PHP script and you can easily do that on your own.\u001b[18X\u001b[24;2H\u001b[72X\r\n*/\u001b[22X\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'base_url'\u001b[m\u000f] = (isset($\u001b[94m_SERVER\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'HTTPS'\u001b[m\u000f]) ? \u001b[92m\"https://\"\u001b[m\u000f : \u001b[92m\"http://\"\u001b[m\u000f) . $\u001b[94m_SERVER\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'HTTP_HOST'\u001b[m\u000f] . ROOT;\r\n\u001b[71X\n/*\u001b[80X\u001b[29;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[30;3HIndex File\u001b[56X\u001b[31;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[32;2H\u001b[70X\u001b[33;3HTypically this will be your index.php file, unless you've renamed it to\u001b[34;2H something else. If you are using mod_rewrite to remove the page set this\u001b[35;3Hvariable so that it is blank.\u001b[37X\u001b[38;10H\u001b[92mindex_page'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'index.php'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[14X\u001b[42;3HURI PROTOCOL\u001b[8X\u001b[45;3HThis item determines which server global should be used to retrieve the\u001b[46;3HURI string.  The default setting of 'REQUEST_URI' works for most servers.\u001b[47;2H If your links do not seem to work, try one of the other delicious flavors:\u001b[48;2H\u001b[60X\u001b[49;3H'REQUEST_URI'    Uses $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI']\u001b[50;2H 'QUERY_STRING'   Uses $_SERVER['QUERY_STRING']\u001b[51;3H'PATH_INFO'      Uses $_SERVER['PATH_INFO']\u001b[53;3HWARNING: If you set this to 'PATH_INFO', URIs will always be URL-decoded!\r\n*/\u001b[42X\r\n$\u001b[94mconfig\u001b[m\u000f[\u001b[92m'uri_protocol'\u001b[m\u000f] = \u001b[92m'REQUEST_URI'\u001b[m\u000f;\u001b[7X\r\n \r\n/*\u001b[64X\u001b[58;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[59;3HURL suffix\u001b[13X\u001b[60;2H--------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n| \r\n| This option allows you to add a suffix to all URLs generated by CodeIgniter.\r\n| For more information please see the user guide:\r\n|\u001b[33X\r\n| https://codeigniter.com/user_guide/general/urls.html\u001b[66;224H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f,1            Top\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
